A: The problem is that you are calling dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator().next() in your loop. This will always return the first child because you are creating a new iterator in each loop iteration.
Instead, you should use the iterator you get from dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator() in your loop.
Here is the corrected code:
names=new ArrayList<>();
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        for (Iterator<DataSnapshot> it = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator(); it.hasNext(); ) {
            i = i + 1;
            names.add(it.next().getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle the error
    }
});

This way, you will get all the values from all children in the names list.

